    public class Vehicle
extends javafx.scene.shape.Circle
    Class Vehicle represents specific vehicle shown on the map.
    Author:
    Michal Rein, Ondřej Motyčka

      • Vehicle

        public Vehicle(TransportLine transportLine,
               javafx.scene.paint.Color color,
               java.lang.String number,
               java.lang.Long deploy)
        Create new vehicle, get route, set mark properties, essential coordinates and calculate direction towards first stop.
        Parameters:
        transportLine - TransportLine class that the vehicle is part of.
        color - Color of vehicle shown on the map.
        number - Unique number of vehicle.
        deploy - Time (is seconds format) when vehicle should be deployed.

    • Method Detail

      • calculateTrajectory

        public void calculateTrajectory()
        Calculates trajectory of vehicle and sets it's new layout coordinates

      • waitOnStop

        public void waitOnStop()
        Called when vehicle reached a stop. Auxiliary stops are passed, regular stops invoke counter, which simulates 60 seconds period of waiting at a stop.

      • calculateDirection

        public void calculateDirection()
        Calculates direction to a next stop. If stops are on two different streets, determine which end of current street neighbours with street of the next stop and set direction towards that neighbouring end. There should always be a regular or an auxiliary (invisible) stop on any of neighbouring streets.

      • createTimetable

        public void createTimetable()
        Creates timetable by calculating estimated times of arrival between stops. A new timetable is created when vehicle is created and each time it reaches any end of the route (start or end stops).

      • getRoute

        public java.util.List<java.util.AbstractMap.SimpleImmutableEntry<Street,Stop>> getRoute()

      • getCurrentStopIndex

        public int getCurrentStopIndex()
        Get index of the next stop to which vehicle is moving towards. By accessing route list with this index, next stop will always be returned.
        Returns:
        Index for accessing next stop in the route list.
